5. Understanding the Software Supply Chain

The software supply chain describes how software moves from developers to end users.

A simplified flow looks like this:

Developer
      │
      ▼
Writes a Package
      │
      ▼
Publishes to Package Registry
      │
      ▼
Developers Install the Package
      │
      ▼
Application is Built
      │
      ▼
Application is Deployed
      │
      ▼
Users Use the Application

Every step introduces potential security risks.

Why the Software Supply Chain Matters

If an attacker compromises a widely used package, every application that depends on it may also become compromised.

This makes the software supply chain an attractive target for attackers.

